4. **Free List Management**: Demonstrates the LIFO behavior of the internal free list
5. **Fallback Behavior**: Comments show how exceeding element capacity would trigger `new()` fallback

The implementation correctly uses the public interface (`allocate()`/`deallocate()`) to demonstrate the internal push/pop mechanics without directly accessing private methods, as specified in the assessment objectives.

